---
description: when testing UI in Shopware 6 Admin or Storefront
alwaysApply: false
---

- After adding product to cart, verify it was added before proceeding.
- After a page transition, assert a stable content element is visible before the next interaction so the view is
  actually mounted.
- When changing pages or tabs, wait for a heading or other anchor inside the target view (not only the shell).
- Do not wait for network idle on admin; background polling keeps the network busy.
- After clicks that toggle Vue state (e.g. customer Edit), wait for a primary signal (enabled control, class change)
  with a timeout well above 5s before asserting dependent controls.
- Hash-only navigation (`location.hash` or `page.goto('/admin#/…')`) can change the URL without running Vue Router;
  boot `/admin`, wait for `.sw-desktop`, then `Shopware.Application.view.router.push` (name + params or path)
  and `waitForURL` on the hash.
- Prefer a single root locator when Shopware duplicates a page class on an inner wrapper (
  e.g. `div.sw-page.sw-customer-detail` or `div.sw-page.sw-users-permissions-role-detail`) to avoid strict-mode
  violations.
- Dockerized Playwright (NVM, pnpm, browsers, shell exit codes) lives in `docker-exec.mdc` in this folder.
